AIM: To write a c program to simulate producer consumer problem using a 
semaphore.

THEORY:
The produces consumer problem is a classic example of a “multi-process 
synchronization”.
It describes the two processes, the produces and the consumer, which share a 
common, fixed size buffer used as a queue.
The producer job is to generate date, put it into the buffer and start again.
The consumer consumes the data, one place at a time.
Here , we are give again using threads, as well as semaphore variables like full, 
empty.
The common buffer here, we are using in produces[100] pthread_mutex_t
to PTHREAD_MUTER_INITIALIZER.
And here also, we using pthread_multex_lock to provide locks for the producer as 
well as the consumer and pthread_create and pthread_join is for creating and using 
of threads.


PROGRAM:
#include<stdio.h>
#include<stdlib.h>
#include<sys/types.h>
#include<pthread.h>
#define size 10
Int full=0,k=0,empty=size, count=-1,products[size];
pthread_mutex_t clock=PTHREAD_MUTEX_INITIALIZER;
pthread_mutex_t clock=PTHREAD_MUTEX_INITIALIZER;
void *produce(void *ptr){
int item=rand()%100;
while(full==size)
sleep(1);
thread_mutex_lock(&plock);
full++;
products[++count]=item;
printf(“%d item is produced \n ”, item);
empty--;
sleep(1);
pthread_mutex_unlock(&plock);
}
void *consume(void *per)
{
while(empty==size)
sleep(1);
pthread_mutex_lock(&clock);
empty++;
printf(“%d item is consumed \n ”,products[count--]);
full--;
sleep(2);
pthread_mutex_unlock(&clock);
}
int main()
{
Int i,n_prod,n_con;
pthread_t producers[10],consumers[10];
printf(“enter number of produces : ”);
scanf(“%d”,&n_prod);
printf(“enter number of consumers : ”);
scanf(“%d”,&n_con);
for(i=0;i<n_prod;i++)
pthread_create(&producers[i],NULL,produce,NULL);
for(i=0;i<n_con;i++)
pthread_create(&consumers[i],NULL,consumer,NULL);
for(i=0;i<n_prod;i++)
pthread_join(producers[i],NULL);
for(i=0;i<n_con;i++)
pthread_join(consumers[i],NULL);
}

Output:
enter number of producers : 5
enter number of consumers : 4
83 item is produced
83 item is consumed
96 item is produced
96 item is consumed
77 item is produced
15 item is consumed
86 item is produced
